bilingual.source: Did he knock on the door first?
If there are people in the meeting room, you are supposed to knock before entering.
bilingual.target: 如果会议室里有人，你应该在进入前敲门。

bilingual.source: The carpenter knock the nails into the wood.
bilingual.target: 木匠把钉子敲进木头里。

bilingual.source: She knock on the table to get everyone's attention.
bilingual.target: 她敲桌子以引起大家的注意。

bilingual.source: I heard someone knock at the door.
He walked to the door to knock at the door.
Please knock at the door before you come in.
He heard a knock at the window late at night.
bilingual.target: 他在深夜听到窗户上有敲击声。

bilingual.source: I knock on the door to see if anyone is home.
bilingual.target: 我敲门看看有没有人在家。

list.abstract: knock（英 [nɒk]，美 [nɑːk]），英语单词，作动词为敲；敲打；撞到。作名词为敲打声；敲门声；撞击。短语搭配有knock down（撞倒, 击倒）。例句为“Easy, girl — you'll knock me over（小心，小姑娘—你会把我撞倒的）！” knock相关近义词有strike、hit。
27日零时，所属社明星帝国通过官方推特公开Nasty Nasty的19禁预告照，预告照中Kevin的果敢露出以及大胆的动作引发好奇。 此外，组合音源将在9月3日公开。

yingyinNormal.en: I used to come out here at night, stare at it, hoping maybe the wind or a bird might knock it down.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我就经常在夜里跑过来看看它，盼着能有风或者鸟把它给弄下来。

yingyinNormal.en: That's not the secret knock. This is the secret knock.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这不是敲门密码，这才是敲门密码。

yingyinNormal.en: Oh. This is so exciting. Oh God. Come and knock on my door. We'll be waiting for you.
yingyinNormal.zh: 好兴奋喔，来敲我的门（《三人行》主题曲）。我们等着你。

yingyinNormal.en: Why don't we just knock on the door and talk to him? I tried. Yeah, the guy's a jerk.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们何不直接去敲那家的门，跟主人谈呢？我试过了，那家伙是个混蛋。

yingyinNormal.en: Penny! Penny! Penny! Sheldon, honey, I've told you, it's a small apartment. You only have to knock one time.
yingyinNormal.zh: 佩妮！佩妮！谢尔顿，亲爱的，我说过房子很小，只要敲一次门就行。

yingyinNormal.en: Okay, I would ring the bell to distract him and then I would knock the gun out of his hand with a Chinese throwing star.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我会按铃铛分散他的注意力，然后我会用中国的飞镖把那个家伙敲昏。

yingyinNormal.en: Rach, Rach? Knock knock. Who's there? I'll tell you at the wedding.
yingyinNormal.zh: 瑞秋，瑞秋, 咚, 咚（敲门声）是谁啊? 在婚礼上我再告诉你。

yingyinNormal.en: Good morning. See? I didn't knock, but it's fine. I didn't knock, but it's fine. I didn't knock, but it's fine.
yingyinNormal.zh: 早上好。看，我没敲门，不过没关系。我没敲门不过没关系，我没敲门不过没关系。

yingyinNormal.en: Knock, knock. Who's there? Our family is an embarrassment. That's not much of a joke.
yingyinNormal.zh: 咚咚，是谁敲门呀？我们家就是个笑话。这算不上是笑话啊。

yingyinNormal.en: Come on, get ready. It's almost time for the Halloween parade. You're supposed to knock!
yingyinNormal.zh: 来吧，准备好。万圣节游行要开始了。你应该敲门的！

yingyinNormal.en: Don't knock. Just walk in. Why be polite to the world's leading expert on the dung beetle?
yingyinNormal.zh: 别敲门，尽管进来吧，对一位世界领先地位的屎克螂专家客气什么啊？

yingyinNormal.en: Fine. You walk up to the house, knock on the door and demand your stuff back. What if he says no?
yingyinNormal.zh: 好吧，你走到门口，敲门然后要你的东西，他要是拒绝怎么办？

yingyinNormal.en: Interesting. If my official residence were across the hall, I wonder if I'd need to knock every time I came over here.
yingyinNormal.zh: 有意思。如果我把寝宫移到了对门，那我回来这里需不需要敲门呢？

yingyinNormal.en: So two years later, there's a knock on the door. Guy opens it, and there on his porch is the snail, who says, "What the heck was all that about?"
yingyinNormal.zh: 两年之后，突然有人敲门了，那人打开门看见门口立着只蜗牛，蜗牛说“这TM是怎么回事？”

yingyinNormal.en: What difference does it make? The whole point of a secret knock is to establish a non-verbal signal to verify the identity of one's co-conspirators.
yingyinNormal.zh: 有什么区别啊？设置敲门密码的所有意义就在于建立一种非语言信号，来验证某人的同行者身份的办法。

yingyinNormal.en: If there's one thing my father taught me, it was, well, to always knock before going into the pool house. But the other thing was, never borrow money.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我爸有教过我，在进入台球间时一定要先敲门。还有, 永远都不要借钱。

yingyinNormal.en: Knock-knock. Who's there? Olive.[I love u] Olive you, too.
yingyinNormal.zh: 咚咚咚。谁呀？橄榄[我爱你]。我也爱你。

yingyinNormal.en: A judge will probably knock this down.
yingyinNormal.zh: 法官会驳回此案吧。

yingyinNormal.en: Knock yourself out, Riley. I'll call it in.
yingyinNormal.zh: 别客气，莱利，我上报去。

yingyinNormal.en: Anyway, my socks are on. Let's knock them off.
yingyinNormal.zh: 总之，我脚上有袜子，快快把它们吓掉吧。

examination_example.sentence: On a five to three vote, the Supreme Court <highlight>knocked</highlight> out much of Arizona's immigration law Monday.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 周一，最高法院以五票对三票否决了亚利桑那州的大部分移民法。

examination_example.sentence: But as Cline is the first to note, it took Beaumont decades to perfect her craft; her example can't be <highlight>knocked</highlight> off.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 但正如克莱因第一个注意到的，博蒙特花了几十年的时间来完善她的工艺；她的榜样是不可复制的。

word_usage.usage: knock作动词时，既可作及物动词，又可作不及物动词。作及物动词时，其后可接名词或者代词，如：knock one's head；作不及物动词时，其后常接介词短语，如：Somebody was knocking on the window. 有人在敲窗户。
knock作名词时，一般用单数，前面加a，如：There was a knock on/at the door. 有敲门声。

examination_example.sentence_trans: 就在去年，我正在班里组织研讨会，突然有人敲教室门。

examination_example.sentence: If someone <highlight>knocks</highlight> and it's not an important matter, excuse yourself and let the person know you're busy.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 如果有人敲门，但不是什么重要的事情，就找个借口，让他知道你很忙。

examination_example.sentence: I didn't think about it much until a morning last week when I <highlight>knocked</highlight> my favorite teapot off the table.

examination_example.sentence: My next-door neighbor, <highlight>knocked</highlight>, asking for help.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我的隔壁邻居敲门，请求帮助。

examination_example.sentence: Who would <highlight>knock</highlight> at his own door if he was staying alone?
examination_example.sentence_trans: 如果他一个人待着，谁会敲他自己的门？

examination_example.sentence: While Nick was watching CCTV News, someone <highlight>knocked</highlight> at the door.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 当尼克正在看中央电视台的新闻时，有人敲门。

examination_example.sentence: At last, he felt ashamed to <highlight>knock</highlight> the tree over.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 最后，他为撞倒这棵树感到羞愧。

examination_example.sentence: No one likes a bad smell that could <highlight>knock</highlight> somebody over.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 没有人喜欢会把人熏倒难闻的气味。

examination_example.sentence: He argued that he had been <highlight>knocked</highlight> down by a runaway team and his leg broken in two places.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他辩称自己被一个失控的车队撞倒，腿断了两处。

examination_example.sentence: Just when she was going to bed, there was a <highlight>knock</highlight> at the door.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 正当她要上床睡觉时，有敲门声。
